<taxonomicName id="1A280882B58C4BC2ED79FED2E5FC5474" LSID="D5411901-06C4-53DE-B981-4F63FFA9A390" authority="LeConte, 1853" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xenogonilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Trechicus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Trechicus">Trechicus LeConte, 1853</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F8AEB85CF84AA99093E2A7ECEDBDC17" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="690D1E9DF53E1FC863A91C2A4B5E6912" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">
<taxonomicName id="FC4B57325208C6ED7FABC436EB77C052" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trechicus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853c: 386. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="430BD5CFDEAFBAAEE7EA5522B2CEB7C0" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbripennis">
<emphasis id="B31ED5818A6C4DA4708CA54296F3D59E" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechicus umbripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853 (= 
<taxonomicName id="4B9D49B82979942B379DAA73190CA504" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="E984B6794F4BF2C52BD2A7FBB76B04BB" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Bembidium nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831) designated by Jeannel (1926: 247). Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4D75ED8E08F00FE7565299398DD99AD2" authorityName="Clairville" authorityYear="1806" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE934C79AC3A8C3536F5F78CFB5312F" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="87063F0391BBCA377760D03E7F724E96" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Greek 
<emphasis id="7E233BE7441E830E0A6A8ECB3D610AA3" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">eicon</emphasis>
(image, figure), probably alluding to the resemblance of the adults to those of 
<taxonomicName id="DED663B8011D83B63144451DD8383A73" authorityName="Clairville" authorityYear="1806" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7D802E8A5B3DCC79C510E1F67B4B11FF" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(&quot;have very much the appearance of minute Trechus&quot;) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C4DA616E5C0BDB0C28DA79F24AD9015" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">
<taxonomicName id="B1E6DE6645576BF99BB1800E6322EE97" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Extromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Extromus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="5B13A791C00BB444483BA6EE72CFFAB0" originalValue="Péringuey">Peringuey</normalizedToken>
, 1896: 584, 586. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="A15FFC98385E14E427A6F8ACCFCB74A7" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Extromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="F3A59498CE93A43272745B35C1E1FDDF" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Extromus pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="730F1C1EB540FFC6FF7610337A27D351" originalValue="Péringuey">Peringuey</normalizedToken>
, 1896 (= 
<taxonomicName id="DF8D7EB31A756635F037DB655F507C7F" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="4D68D1393C6CBC3D99ADD1D037916113" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Bembidium nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831) by monotypy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3A110594BE1CD1011FE06D2E64A93D01" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="CA958E131FB197F0ACD17E360FBC6C4D" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D2FDB2A7E6A2DFFC3BBCFB881A68909" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">
Eighteen species in the Nearctic (one endemic species), Australian (seven endemic species), and Afrotropical (ten endemic species) Regions and one (
<taxonomicName id="025CA0FC5E0CE5B99BEDD7FD243E7DB2" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="DC0AABEEA0C342CB98BA33C195631CB5" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) subcosmopolitan species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ED886AF5526A9C667BDA6064A11F2A13" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" type="identification">
<paragraph id="43BADE69C4C86ABF1DF1A899C8720548" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B5408A274817C5FADBE363E747247C0" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Bousquet (1987a: 128) commented on the structural differences between the two species found in North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4AF688333AB9B804A399C1950005DD17" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="CE003B3C29B707382BEABD2304914278" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E5CDCCC11AB5858FA858703BA955B435" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">
<taxonomicName id="6715AC8DEEDC467F37591A5ECE94D4E5" authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Hirtoperigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B412C99068EB1C0A1C640B922D4C9ED0" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Hirtoperigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Perrault is placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4D4CD3D04845ED6043572A160E6E2584" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4B0C15E3924E21B558ED58EB4DE00BF" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Lorenz (2005: 438). However, the position of the median group of setae of the umbilical series in the type species (
<taxonomicName id="E7A86A5722D3B3D6E12F9EEBAF0C8E1B" authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1988" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tronqueti">
<emphasis id="244F6178293A1334C439B67821A1C93B" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona tronqueti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Perrault from Sri Lanka) and in 
<taxonomicName id="A2AECE95262F629D9E49897DBC7D0F6F" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis id="C4690C973416DFDFC908DAD6A2A396ED" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jeannel (from Vietnam) suggests that members of 
<taxonomicName id="E54B70E454E1D6DB6BB4F69AD38218BC" authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Hirtoperigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5731D9E382A38A6BE60AEF148C2296F4" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Hirtoperigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="A76F43F8FA94C1C5D70E0EC779C1E8F1" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1835" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D04F9830BC5515CA55A3783028EDD2C2" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. than to 
<taxonomicName id="2B347791EA76DFA08A316F44245B088B" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6BA258EFD75FA54363B4FB63E1A2E806" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Perrault (1988) placed a third species (
<taxonomicName id="818072535EC123074A9C017A4DE12901" authorityName="Basilewsky" authorityYear="1953" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis id="3302D7CE998969F2A20499BAFADCD7B2" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Basilewsky from Africa) in 
<taxonomicName id="C32D3FD80A689194F1ADD5E53CB5F6C2" authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Hirtoperigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BC0954163AA73B2A50F704A26B38D90D" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Hirtoperigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the original description alone; according to Basilewsky (1989: 447), the species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="27BAE7FC2DE9CED71692C7715AC8AACA" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="26DCB0B4D9BC3696957CF06B8A485DE1" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6FBEFFAB5B80546554969BA9963B4B3" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">
The relationship of the endemic North American species (
<taxonomicName id="1F1760145ADFA278D258B2F6675FF61A" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipennis">
<emphasis id="627C6451C03E929B6304EC463FC368CC" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona pallipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte) has not been studied and, in my opinion, it may be more closely related to members of 
<taxonomicName id="98E80D2E35D6C14C5EA68EA690292A24" authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Cryptoperigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EF5228D2FCF4878CCBC8190DCE8AB6E9" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Cryptoperigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to those of 
<taxonomicName id="A2094E553D4C2E39C1381BBC1948D2CD" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="37DE74C2E86A4F2625F0FBA707309C03" italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Trechicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
